Complete the following tutorial - 
1. rosrun turtlesim turtlesim_node
	- runs a single node

2. See the list of active nodes and topics
	- rosnode list
	- rostopic list

3. See info about a particular node or topic
	- rosnode info /turtlesim
	- rostopic info /turtle1/cmd_vel

4. rqt
	- To publish to a topic graphically (publish to /turtle1/cmd_vel to see the turtle move)
	- Later write code to publish manually to a topic

5. rosrun rqt_graph rqt_graph 
	- To visualize how all the nodes and topics interact with each other.

6. rostopic echo /turtle1/cmd_vel
	- See topic messages realtime (while you publish using rqt)

7. rosmsg show geometry_msgs/Twist
	- To see the type of each message sent by rqt.
	- Its possible to make your own message type as well. 


References: 
1. http://www.fer.unizg.hr/_download/repository/p03-ros-uvod%5B1%5D.pdf